race.description: Ray White Barossa Valley | Two Wells Mdn Plate
race.comment: ZADOWS LANDING (7) turned in an eye-catching run at Strathalbyn, winding up hard from well back to miss a whisker over 1350m. Raced a well-supported favourite and can go one better up in trip with the blinkers added. EAGLE MOON (1) was on speed and just nudged out in the same race. Has to stretch out over further but is progressing nicely and is sure to give a big sight. OLDPOP (9) has switched yards on an 11-day return. The ear muffs come off as does the tongue tie. Might be looking for this distance now and Holder rides. WINSTON'S PRIDE (11) is a likely improver from a leading stable. Has the rail and Pannell replacing the apprentice is a positive switch.
